                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 20, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190. Your 299, November 19, 6 p.m. Endeavor to obtain the elimination from the
                    Enabling Act, Article 1, of the phrase “with the Government of the United States
                    of America.” The phrase is apparently a limitation on the grant of power and is
                    inconsistent with the actual procedure. This Government does not desire to
                    negotiate an agreement as indicated. It is in fact understood that Funding
                    Agreement has practically been negotiated by the Brazilian Government with the
                    National Foreign Trade Council (acting on behalf of such creditors as shall by
                    acceptance of its terms become parties thereto). The Council has applied to the
                    Export-Import Bank for a commitment to participate in the financing of notes
                    issued under the Funding Agreement and the Bank yesterday announced the matter
                    and the extent to which it would agree to such participation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
